text.style: font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; font-weight: normal; fill: #000000; line-height: 15px;
text.tspan: 1. something that you very much want to achieve
2. a formal request to do something or have something , example
find a job
3. an arrangement between a bank and a customer that allows
the customer to pay in and take out money
4. the person who employs you or who is in charge of you at
work
5. job or profession that you have been trained for, and which
you do for a long period of your life
6. one of a group of people who work together
7. a business organization that makes or sells goods or services
8. a group of people who work together in a particular part of a
large organization such as a hospital, university, company, or
government
9. to have earned something by good or bad actions or behaviour
10. to receive a particular amount of money for the work that you
do
11. the state of being known about by a lot of people because of
your achievements
12. challenge
13. to make someone feel admiration and respect
14. the money that you earn from your work or that you receive
from
15. the large-scale production of goods or of substances such as
coal and steel
16. a formal meeting at which someone is asked questions in
order to find out whether they are suitable for a job, course of
study etc
17. to ask someone questions
18. the person who directs or controls a group, organization,
country etc
19. someone whose job is to manage part or all of a company or
other organization
20. an amount of money paid regularly by the government or
company to someone who does not work any more, for example
because they have reached the age when people stop working or
because they are ill
21. the situation or experience of being poor
22. an attempt to __________ someone by using influence,
arguments, or threats
23. having happened or existed before the event, time, or thing
that you are talking about now
24. a job that needs a high level of education and training
25. to stop working, usually because you have reached a certain
age
26. money that you receive as payment from the organization
you work for, usually paid to you every month
27. the people who work for an organization
28. a period of time during which people refuse to work , as a
protest
29. an amount of money that you must pay to the government
according to your income, property, goods etc and that is used to
pay for public services
30. to make someone pay a tax
31. having a lot of money
